1
00:00:00,966 --> 00:00:02,766
It's Yu Jun's first time at the beach.

2
00:00:02,766 --> 00:00:03,733
I know.

3
00:00:03,734 --> 00:00:05,206
That's the ocean.

4
00:00:05,951 --> 00:00:07,333
I also haven't been to the beach
in forever.

5
00:00:07,333 --> 00:00:09,566
How are they only in shorts and shirts?

6
00:00:09,566 --> 00:00:11,433
You don't get cold when you're a kid.

7
00:00:11,866 --> 00:00:12,666
That looks fun.

8
00:00:14,333 --> 00:00:15,407
Why don't you work on your feet?

9
00:00:15,900 --> 00:00:18,900
(Yu Jun's first time
at the beach and on the sand)

10
00:00:19,466 --> 00:00:20,833
(What is this? It feels so weird!)

11
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:25,200
(Yu Jun tripped over himself
from the weird feeling of the sand.)

12
00:00:25,366 --> 00:00:27,166
You're so cute.

13
00:00:27,566 --> 00:00:29,666
- It's hard to walk on sand, isn't it?
- My gosh!

14
00:00:30,633 --> 00:00:32,000
That was adorable just now.

15
00:00:32,366 --> 00:00:36,366
- Yu Jun, this isn't like asphalt.
- It feels odd, doesn't it?

16
00:00:36,366 --> 00:00:38,033
I'd better hold him up.

17
00:00:38,333 --> 00:00:39,600
Hold my arm tightly.

18
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:40,533
Oh, goodness.

19
00:00:40,933 --> 00:00:42,100
Let's go.

20
00:00:43,900 --> 00:00:45,266
He can't push it!

21
00:00:45,266 --> 00:00:46,866
The cart won't move forward in the sand.

22
00:00:46,866 --> 00:00:48,400
Okay.

23
00:00:48,400 --> 00:00:49,966
He's getting irritated
because he can't push it.

24
00:00:50,733 --> 00:00:52,733
Do you really think that's going to help?

25
00:00:52,733 --> 00:00:54,800
- No, not like that.
- Let's go.

26
00:00:56,566 --> 00:01:00,566
(I can go anywhere
with my uncles and my cart!)

27
00:01:00,566 --> 00:01:02,900
(The cart helper and Yu Jun's bodyguard)

28
00:01:02,900 --> 00:01:05,966
(The uncles are basically doing
all the work with the cart.)

29
00:01:06,333 --> 00:01:10,033
(He's like an astronaut
landing on the moon for the first time.)

30
00:01:10,466 --> 00:01:11,633
Should we go the other way?

31
00:01:11,633 --> 00:01:12,900
Do you want to turn around?

32
00:01:13,266 --> 00:01:16,033
(They walked all the way here
with the cart.)

33
00:01:16,033 --> 00:01:18,100
(I can't push it.)

34
00:01:18,100 --> 00:01:19,766
We have to keep going.

35
00:01:20,133 --> 00:01:22,666
Yu Jun, how is it
to be at the beach for the first time?

36
00:01:23,100 --> 00:01:24,785
Let me interview you.

37
00:01:24,900 --> 00:01:25,933
How do you feel?

38
00:01:26,833 --> 00:01:29,633
He's telling you to stop
and focus on pushing the cart.

39
00:01:30,633 --> 00:01:32,300
Good boy!

40
00:01:32,566 --> 00:01:34,000
Let's go!

41
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:35,333
Shake some sand off.

42
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:37,900
Let's take a little break, Yu Jun.

43
00:01:37,900 --> 00:01:39,566
(Pausing the sand exploration
to save the uncles' backs)

44
00:01:39,566 --> 00:01:41,666
Yu Jun, let's ditch the cart...

45
00:01:42,466 --> 00:01:43,333
Oh, gosh.

46
00:01:44,466 --> 00:01:45,333
Now is the time!

47
00:01:46,314 --> 00:01:48,966
(Since we are here,
let's do something more fun than this!)

48
00:01:49,811 --> 00:01:51,133
Let's go!

49
00:01:52,833 --> 00:01:55,066
You had no idea
you could play in sand, did you?

50
00:01:56,166 --> 00:01:58,466
- There's sand!
- We're really playing in the sand.

51
00:01:59,266 --> 00:02:01,466
We couldn't do this in the living room.

52
00:02:01,933 --> 00:02:04,200
(A successful play session in the sand
that they failed with at home)

53
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:05,500
(Digging away)

54
00:02:05,553 --> 00:02:06,941
HUENINGKAI is going all out again.

55
00:02:06,966 --> 00:02:09,100
(Suddenly waging a battle on sand)

56
00:02:09,100 --> 00:02:10,666
Yu Jun, you should race HUENINGKAI.

57
00:02:11,333 --> 00:02:12,733
(A race to dig the sand)

58
00:02:12,733 --> 00:02:13,500
There you go!
Are you having fun?

59
00:02:15,366 --> 00:02:16,233
He's shaking it off.

60
00:02:16,233 --> 00:02:17,933
(Attacking with sand)

61
00:02:19,033 --> 00:02:20,833
(One more time!)

62
00:02:23,933 --> 00:02:24,766
This is fun.
(This is so exciting!)

63
00:02:26,266 --> 00:02:27,466
He's throwing sand at you guys.

64
00:02:28,366 --> 00:02:29,166
Do you see this?

65
00:02:29,166 --> 00:02:31,366
This is the power of a 14-month-old.

66
00:02:31,833 --> 00:02:34,233
And this is the power of a 26-year-old.

67
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:37,500
(This is unfair!)

68
00:02:38,766 --> 00:02:39,600
Oh, sorry.

69
00:02:39,966 --> 00:02:42,566
Yu Jun, you're in my way
when I'm trying to play with the sand.

70
00:02:42,566 --> 00:02:44,433
Can you take two steps back?

71
00:02:45,133 --> 00:02:46,066
This is fun.

72
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:48,866
In 1, 2, 3.

73
00:02:48,866 --> 00:02:51,000
(I'll be nice and listen just this once.)

74
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:52,733
I see something!
There's something in the sand.

75
00:02:54,733 --> 00:02:55,966
It's mud now.

76
00:02:56,566 --> 00:02:57,700
I see rocks.

77
00:02:58,800 --> 00:03:00,466
Can you ask them
if we can borrow their shovels?

78
00:03:00,466 --> 00:03:01,833
Should we ask them?

79
00:03:01,833 --> 00:03:04,666
I want to see the end of this tunnel.

80
00:03:06,333 --> 00:03:08,400
What country would we reach
if we dug to the other side of Earth?

81
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:10,433
- Which way?
- Isn't it Argentina?

82
00:03:10,433 --> 00:03:12,266
Yu Jun, do you want to go to Argentina?

83
00:03:12,933 --> 00:03:15,100
I want to take a photo
with Yu Jun in the hole.

84
00:03:16,033 --> 00:03:17,133
Should we fit him in?

85
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:19,366
Should we try?

86
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:21,733
- For just one photo?
- Just one?

87
00:03:22,666 --> 00:03:24,433
Come here, Yu Jun!

88
00:03:24,433 --> 00:03:25,566
- Yu Jun.
- Do you want to go in?

89
00:03:25,566 --> 00:03:26,733
This is fun!

90
00:03:26,733 --> 00:03:27,766
Come in, Yu Jun.

91
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:30,433
Here comes Yu Jun's big entry.

92
00:03:30,433 --> 00:03:31,966
In 1, 2, 3.

93
00:03:33,933 --> 00:03:35,333
This is so much fun!

94
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:36,800
You can pull yourself out.

95
00:03:37,900 --> 00:03:39,986
- You can climb out on your own.
- How are you going to do that?

96
00:03:41,772 --> 00:03:43,806
Get him out now.

97
00:03:44,866 --> 00:03:47,766
We could dig a hole as big as Yu Jun
if we dug a little more.

98
00:03:47,766 --> 00:03:49,166
- It's already at his height.
- I know.

99
00:03:49,166 --> 00:03:50,433
(Checking the photo)

100
00:03:52,500 --> 00:03:55,500
(He got the cutest photo,
thanks to the uncles.)

101
00:03:56,200 --> 00:03:57,333
Yu Jun, your neck must feel chilly.

102
00:03:58,200 --> 00:03:59,400
Here's your scarf.

103
00:04:00,300 --> 00:04:02,933
(Using his shirt as a temporary scarf)

104
00:04:04,333 --> 00:04:06,933
This is an impressive hole
for the shovels we have.

105
00:04:06,933 --> 00:04:08,966
Seriously. I can't believe we dug so deep
with these tiny shovels.

106
00:04:08,966 --> 00:04:10,366
We deserve some credit.

107
00:04:12,433 --> 00:04:16,166
(Yu Jun is taking a walk
with Uncle SOOBIN.)

108
00:04:17,333 --> 00:04:19,333
(Still digging the hole)

109
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:23,800
I basically have to dive into it
to keep digging now.

110
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:25,733
Yes, we have to put our heads in now.

111
00:04:28,100 --> 00:04:29,833
Should we make a booby trap with this?

112
00:04:29,833 --> 00:04:30,766
That sounds perfect!

113
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:34,233
(The uncles can have fun.
I'm going on a walk.)

114
00:04:34,233 --> 00:04:35,166
It's hard to walk, isn't it?

115
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:38,366
(Wobbly)

116
00:04:41,100 --> 00:04:42,500
Let's play rock-paper-scissors,

117
00:04:43,266 --> 00:04:46,633
and the loser has to jump
to where the winner points.

118
00:04:46,633 --> 00:04:47,466
Great idea.

119
00:04:48,900 --> 00:04:50,500
Rock, paper, scissors.

120
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:51,500
(HUENINGKAI's booby trap game)

121
00:04:51,766 --> 00:04:53,800
Rock, paper, scissors.

122
00:04:54,333 --> 00:04:55,633
Rock, paper, scissors.

123
00:04:55,633 --> 00:04:57,733
(BEOMGYU is safe.)

124
00:04:57,733 --> 00:04:58,766
It's you two now.

125
00:04:58,766 --> 00:05:00,133
Rock, paper, scissors.

126
00:05:01,066 --> 00:05:03,233
- How can we make this funny?
- Go here.

127
00:05:03,233 --> 00:05:04,533
Yu Jun, they're doing something fun.

128
00:05:04,533 --> 00:05:05,533
- Look.
- Watch your ankles.
Be careful.

129
00:05:06,333 --> 00:05:07,600
Make sure to flex your feet hard.

130
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:08,500
Look at them.

131
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:09,576
(Two spectators to watch the fun)

132
00:05:13,433 --> 00:05:14,366
That was spot-on.

133
00:05:14,733 --> 00:05:16,600
- You remembered where it was.
- Yes.

134
00:05:16,866 --> 00:05:19,133
(They sure look
like they're having a blast.)

135
00:05:19,133 --> 00:05:20,200
(They filled the hole back.)

136
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:21,233
That was fun.

137
00:05:22,300 --> 00:05:25,400
(You guys seemed to have more fun
than Yu Jun did.)

138
00:05:25,966 --> 00:05:27,700
(I had fun too.)

139
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:36,633
We have to have seafood noodle soup
when in Incheon.

140
00:05:36,658 --> 00:05:38,491
(Dinnertime, 5:30 p.m.)

141
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:43,166
There's Yu Jun in Incheon

142
00:05:43,166 --> 00:05:44,266
For Yu Jun...

143
00:05:44,266 --> 00:05:45,733
Can someone get his chair?

144
00:05:47,266 --> 00:05:48,800
Let's go with pink today.

145
00:05:49,100 --> 00:05:51,366
Let's take this chair
and have someone sit there.

146
00:05:51,366 --> 00:05:53,000
- Yu Jun can sit in the middle.
- Sure.

147
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:55,266
- Let's sit!
- One foot in!

148
00:05:55,266 --> 00:05:56,966
(Here comes Yu Jun!)

149
00:05:57,866 --> 00:05:59,000
Yu Jun, you're the youngest, right?

150
00:05:59,000 --> 00:05:59,766
Set the table.

151
00:05:59,766 --> 00:06:01,466
What are you doing?
Start setting the table.

152
00:06:01,966 --> 00:06:03,966
- You have to pour water for us.
- He's so confused.

153
00:06:03,966 --> 00:06:06,199
What were you thinking about
while watching the waves?

154
00:06:06,466 --> 00:06:09,200
"I already knew I was tiny
among the uncles,"

155
00:06:09,200 --> 00:06:11,766
"but I feel even smaller
compared to the ocean."

156
00:06:12,713 --> 00:06:13,940
You don't get what he's saying, do you?

157
00:06:14,400 --> 00:06:15,400
Should we change his diaper?

158
00:06:15,400 --> 00:06:16,800
Yu Jun, go and get your diaper changed.

159
00:06:18,066 --> 00:06:19,333
- Hey.
- Why?

160
00:06:19,333 --> 00:06:21,033
- We have a big issue.
- What?

161
00:06:21,500 --> 00:06:22,833
It's a onesie.

162
00:06:22,833 --> 00:06:24,233
(He's wearing a onesie.)

163
00:06:24,566 --> 00:06:25,752
We have to take the whole thing off.

164
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:27,600
We have to take his shoes off first.

165
00:06:28,566 --> 00:06:29,466
We have to take it all off.

166
00:06:29,833 --> 00:06:30,733
Let's go.

167
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:33,200
(Help me!)

168
00:06:33,633 --> 00:06:34,566
Sorry, Yu Jun.

169
00:06:35,366 --> 00:06:37,866
But we have no choice.

170
00:06:37,866 --> 00:06:39,366
(Firm HUENINGKAI)

171
00:06:40,100 --> 00:06:43,200
(The uncles are calmly starting
from the arms.)

172
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:45,833
- Hey!
- What?

173
00:06:46,766 --> 00:06:48,600
- We didn't need to take it off.
- Why not?

174
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:49,400
Oh!

175
00:06:50,900 --> 00:06:52,266
Okay. Sorry, Yu Jun.

176
00:06:52,866 --> 00:06:55,066
You weren't crying
because you didn't want to take it off.

177
00:06:55,066 --> 00:06:57,066
You cried to tell us
that there were buttons below.

178
00:06:58,233 --> 00:07:01,300
(That's yet another new lesson
learned today.)

179
00:07:01,300 --> 00:07:02,200
Let's go.

180
00:07:02,933 --> 00:07:04,133
(Crying)

181
00:07:04,133 --> 00:07:06,033
(Yu Jun is so close to starting to cry.)

182
00:07:06,033 --> 00:07:07,100
I know.

183
00:07:07,400 --> 00:07:11,266
- I know.
- I feel like you're crying even more...

184
00:07:11,266 --> 00:07:13,566
because you see yourself crying
in the mirror.

185
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:15,800
But you're not sad at all.

186
00:07:16,400 --> 00:07:17,533
You're going to...

187
00:07:17,533 --> 00:07:22,533
Stay with me, one more day and another

188
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:25,833
(The others are just enjoying the view
at the table.)

189
00:07:33,466 --> 00:07:36,533
(They know how tough it's going,
even without watching them.)

190
00:07:37,133 --> 00:07:38,800
BEOMGYU's voice is getting louder...

191
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:40,366
after Yu Jun's cry.

192
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:45,900
(It's because he's using his voice
to change the diaper.)

193
00:07:47,833 --> 00:07:48,933
He feels refreshed.

194
00:07:48,933 --> 00:07:50,866
(Give me food.)

195
00:07:50,866 --> 00:07:52,238
Look how happy you are!

196
00:07:53,233 --> 00:07:55,400
(Time to enjoy Yu Jun's cuteness)

197
00:07:56,333 --> 00:07:57,166
Wink!

198
00:07:58,266 --> 00:07:59,666
(That's easy!)

199
00:07:59,666 --> 00:08:00,800
Can you still do that?

200
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:01,900
Say, "I love you!"

201
00:08:02,866 --> 00:08:04,000
- No?
- Not anymore?

202
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:06,466
He's over that now.

203
00:08:06,466 --> 00:08:08,200
- It was a fad.
- Was that a limited edition?

204
00:08:09,533 --> 00:08:11,733
(Here comes the uncles' food!)

205
00:08:11,733 --> 00:08:12,833
That looks so good.

206
00:08:12,833 --> 00:08:14,000
It's alive!

207
00:08:14,366 --> 00:08:15,300
Look at that.

208
00:08:15,833 --> 00:08:16,900
It moves!

209
00:08:17,966 --> 00:08:20,466
- Let's eat.
- Let's eat!

210
00:08:20,733 --> 00:08:21,600
Do you feel crammed?

211
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:22,833
Do you want to get out?

212
00:08:22,833 --> 00:08:24,933
(Yes, get me out!)

213
00:08:25,933 --> 00:08:28,400
Can we keep him out
just until his food arrives?

214
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:29,333
- Sure.
- Okay.

215
00:08:31,033 --> 00:08:33,133
Let's put his pants on properly.

216
00:08:34,133 --> 00:08:35,466
(The diaper changer wants to fix
the buttons.)

217
00:08:35,466 --> 00:08:37,700
Mom!

218
00:08:37,700 --> 00:08:39,433
- There it is!
- I don't know how to fix it.

219
00:08:39,433 --> 00:08:41,500
- Just wear it like a skirt.
- There's your food.

220
00:08:42,500 --> 00:08:43,533
(Yu Jun's food is ready too!)

221
00:08:43,533 --> 00:08:46,066
- Thank you.
- Thank you!

222
00:08:46,066 --> 00:08:48,366
- We have to wait a bit first.
- We have to cool it.

223
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:52,533
(Preparing the steamed eggs)

224
00:08:52,533 --> 00:08:54,900
Can you get a bit of rice in his bowl
and cool it?

225
00:08:55,433 --> 00:08:58,400
(Yes, sir!
I'll get right on it for Yu Jun!)

226
00:08:59,633 --> 00:09:01,733
(His chubby feet are
slowly climbing onto the table.)

227
00:09:01,733 --> 00:09:03,766
Hey, you can't put your feet on the table!

228
00:09:05,266 --> 00:09:07,800
(Not a chance!)

229
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:09,966
My dad scolded me
whenever I did this as a kid.

230
00:09:10,433 --> 00:09:14,600
(But I'm getting bored
waiting for my food.)

231
00:09:16,333 --> 00:09:19,000
(Cutting the steamed eggs
for 2 minutes and 30 seconds)

232
00:09:19,566 --> 00:09:20,933
Are you making powdered eggs?

233
00:09:20,933 --> 00:09:23,433
He couldn't even eat a grain of rice.
I have to make tiny pieces.

234
00:09:23,433 --> 00:09:24,833
- That's true.
- Let's go back.

235
00:09:24,833 --> 00:09:26,300
You have to get ready to eat.

236
00:09:27,866 --> 00:09:30,666
(Are we eating now?)

237
00:09:32,366 --> 00:09:33,766
(Look at Yu Jun waiting like a good boy.)

238
00:09:33,766 --> 00:09:34,733
This looks great.

239
00:09:36,833 --> 00:09:37,633
(That looks good!)

240
00:09:37,633 --> 00:09:40,200
(Leaning forward as if he's under a spell)

241
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:42,500
Yu Jun leaned forward
as soon as he saw the seaweed flakes.

242
00:09:42,966 --> 00:09:44,800
- It's so good.
- Are you drooling yet?

243
00:09:45,700 --> 00:09:46,666
Can I have some?

244
00:09:46,666 --> 00:09:48,000
(Give me some already!)

245
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:49,733
Okay, wait.

246
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:54,966
(Finally, the first bite
with seaweed flakes)

247
00:09:54,966 --> 00:09:55,900
That was too much.

248
00:09:58,122 --> 00:09:59,788
You want some pancakes, BEOMGYU?

249
00:09:59,788 --> 00:10:02,020
(Trying again with a better portion)

250
00:10:02,855 --> 00:10:04,288
- There you go.
- I'll put this here.

251
00:10:04,288 --> 00:10:05,922
(Will Yu Jun like it?)

252
00:10:07,722 --> 00:10:09,122
What's with that face?

253
00:10:09,122 --> 00:10:10,155
Does he like it or not?

254
00:10:10,822 --> 00:10:11,955
Why doesn't he seem happy?

255
00:10:11,955 --> 00:10:12,955
(Give me more.)

256
00:10:12,955 --> 00:10:14,122
He likes it. He wants more.

257
00:10:17,488 --> 00:10:21,122
(What's this crispy and savory taste?)

258
00:10:22,288 --> 00:10:26,622
(What's this refreshing and spicy flavor?)

259
00:10:28,655 --> 00:10:29,755
(More!)

260
00:10:30,022 --> 00:10:32,122
I think he likes it.
He keeps asking for more.

261
00:10:32,588 --> 00:10:34,155
Let's switch off feeding him.

262
00:10:34,155 --> 00:10:35,355
- Sure.
- Okay.

263
00:10:35,355 --> 00:10:36,488
- Let's take turns...
- Let's switch.

264
00:10:36,488 --> 00:10:37,588
- feeding him.
- Okay.

265
00:10:37,955 --> 00:10:39,622
An abalone for you
for working hard, SOOBIN.

266
00:10:40,322 --> 00:10:41,355
Nice.

267
00:10:42,255 --> 00:10:43,255
(Let's see how it tastes.)

268
00:10:43,255 --> 00:10:44,755
Thank you.

269
00:10:45,188 --> 00:10:46,322
No, I'll do it for you.

270
00:10:47,055 --> 00:10:48,688
I just realized today...

271
00:10:48,688 --> 00:10:51,222
that KAI knows exactly
how to play with the baby.

272
00:10:51,222 --> 00:10:52,622
But I'm not sure
if it's really for the baby.

273
00:10:52,622 --> 00:10:53,622
I'm the one having more fun.
(Maybe it's for adults.)

274
00:10:54,455 --> 00:10:55,888
I was so surprised...

275
00:10:55,888 --> 00:10:57,422
when he came with bubbles on his head.

276
00:10:57,422 --> 00:11:00,022
Babies loved it
when I played with them like that.

277
00:11:00,722 --> 00:11:01,722
(Making a noise)

278
00:11:02,055 --> 00:11:03,055
One more.

279
00:11:03,122 --> 00:11:04,122
Okay.

280
00:11:04,522 --> 00:11:05,522
(Babbling)

281
00:11:05,788 --> 00:11:08,155
(The little good eater likes the taste
and babbles a lot.)

282
00:11:08,955 --> 00:11:10,055
(Babbling)

283
00:11:10,055 --> 00:11:11,055
Are you a Marine?

284
00:11:11,122 --> 00:11:12,122
(Making noises)

285
00:11:12,555 --> 00:11:13,955
(Oh, Uncles are babbling too.)

286
00:11:14,455 --> 00:11:16,322
(Choi Yu Jun, the baby eagle)

287
00:11:16,322 --> 00:11:17,322
Yu Jun.

288
00:11:17,855 --> 00:11:18,955
Swallow first before opening wide.

289
00:11:18,955 --> 00:11:19,955
(Caring about manners)

290
00:11:19,955 --> 00:11:21,422
- He must really like it.
- I know.

291
00:11:21,422 --> 00:11:22,422
He's so happy.
Exactly.

292
00:11:23,422 --> 00:11:24,722
(The food tastes great as always.)

293
00:11:24,988 --> 00:11:26,288
Why is he suddenly feeling good?

294
00:11:26,622 --> 00:11:28,688
Of course he is.

295
00:11:28,688 --> 00:11:29,888
It's his first time at the beach.

296
00:11:29,888 --> 00:11:31,755
He felt uncomfortable earlier,
but got his diaper changed.

297
00:11:31,755 --> 00:11:33,522
- There's delicious food in front.
- Yu Jun.

298
00:11:33,522 --> 00:11:34,922
- You're right.
- And the view is amazing.

299
00:11:34,922 --> 00:11:37,755
Yu Jun, go swim out there
and bring YEONJUN back.

300
00:11:39,655 --> 00:11:40,922
(Uncle YEONJUN?)

301
00:11:41,288 --> 00:11:42,522
He must be up in the air.

302
00:11:42,755 --> 00:11:43,755
There you go.

303
00:11:43,755 --> 00:11:44,888
(Let me eat first.)

304
00:11:44,888 --> 00:11:45,888
Open up.

305
00:11:48,422 --> 00:11:49,755
(Humming)

306
00:11:49,755 --> 00:11:50,755
He likes it.

307
00:11:52,288 --> 00:11:53,622
Yu Jun, you're swallowing too fast.

308
00:11:54,555 --> 00:11:55,555
He's kind of like me.

309
00:11:56,122 --> 00:11:57,122
Exactly.

310
00:11:57,288 --> 00:11:59,988
- He doesn't chew first.
- It's not good to eat so fast...

311
00:12:00,288 --> 00:12:02,655
- if it becomes a habit.
- Where do I put the chili paste?

312
00:12:03,322 --> 00:12:04,322
Here.

313
00:12:04,588 --> 00:12:05,588
Wait.

314
00:12:07,488 --> 00:12:09,722
(You can never relax
when you're parenting.)

315
00:12:09,722 --> 00:12:10,722
Should I feed you, SOOBIN?

316
00:12:10,722 --> 00:12:11,755
No, it's all right.

317
00:12:12,155 --> 00:12:13,822
(I'm fine as long as Yu Jun is okay.)

318
00:12:13,822 --> 00:12:14,822
Is it so delicious?

319
00:12:15,055 --> 00:12:16,055
He's so hyped.

320
00:12:17,855 --> 00:12:21,622
(Giving seaweed flakes to Yu Jun
instead of eating his abalone)

321
00:12:22,422 --> 00:12:23,422
Should I do it for you?

322
00:12:23,788 --> 00:12:24,788
Yes.

323
00:12:27,155 --> 00:12:31,688
(Tasting the abalone after 20 minutes)

324
00:12:34,655 --> 00:12:36,588
Alternate between the egg and the rice.

325
00:12:36,588 --> 00:12:37,588
Okay.

326
00:12:37,755 --> 00:12:40,055
(Let's eat with Uncle BEOMGYU this time.)

327
00:12:40,055 --> 00:12:41,322
He's a great eater.

328
00:12:41,655 --> 00:12:42,688
He must like the food.

329
00:12:42,688 --> 00:12:43,688
(Yum.)
Do you like it?

330
00:12:45,122 --> 00:12:48,022
(The airplane is back.)

331
00:12:48,355 --> 00:12:49,488
Delicious!

332
00:12:50,088 --> 00:12:51,088
You want noodles?

333
00:12:51,088 --> 00:12:52,155
Yes, give me some.

334
00:12:52,322 --> 00:12:53,788
- Are they okay?
- Yes, they're freaking good.

335
00:12:53,788 --> 00:12:54,822
- Really?
- Yes.

336
00:12:55,422 --> 00:12:57,055
- It's best to eat them now.
- So tasty!

337
00:12:57,055 --> 00:12:58,255
They'll get soggy.

338
00:12:58,488 --> 00:12:59,488
Okay.

339
00:13:00,055 --> 00:13:01,055
- I'll give it a try.
- Sure.

340
00:13:01,055 --> 00:13:02,155
(Not that.)

341
00:13:02,622 --> 00:13:03,988
This one? You just want this?

342
00:13:04,022 --> 00:13:05,122
He must like the eggs.

343
00:13:06,122 --> 00:13:07,855
You really know what's good.

344
00:13:07,855 --> 00:13:08,955
He loves the eggs.

345
00:13:08,955 --> 00:13:10,888
(The foodie and the great eater
who chomps on his food)

346
00:13:11,088 --> 00:13:12,822
Look at Yu Jun.

347
00:13:13,155 --> 00:13:14,888
He's so cute when he leans in for a bite.

348
00:13:14,888 --> 00:13:16,322
- This one?
- He looks like a turtle.

349
00:13:17,088 --> 00:13:18,622
Try the pancake too. It's so good.

350
00:13:18,622 --> 00:13:19,622
Okay.

351
00:13:20,088 --> 00:13:21,755
(Yu Jun takes a big bite.)

352
00:13:22,255 --> 00:13:24,655
(Uncle also takes a big bite.)

353
00:13:24,655 --> 00:13:25,655
(Or not.)

354
00:13:26,022 --> 00:13:27,022
So hot!

355
00:13:27,155 --> 00:13:28,955
Yu Jun, let's have some rice now.

356
00:13:29,388 --> 00:13:30,588
Delicious?

357
00:13:31,422 --> 00:13:33,022
Is it tasty? I guess he likes it.

358
00:13:33,255 --> 00:13:34,755
(How about rice?)

359
00:13:35,188 --> 00:13:36,188
No? Not this?

360
00:13:36,188 --> 00:13:37,288
Really?

361
00:13:37,755 --> 00:13:38,988
He used to like rice,

362
00:13:38,988 --> 00:13:40,922
but I guess eggs are his favorite now
after tasting them.

363
00:13:40,922 --> 00:13:41,922
(He's the famous egg lover.)

364
00:13:41,922 --> 00:13:43,088
How about this now?

365
00:13:43,088 --> 00:13:44,255
(Still pushing the rice)

366
00:13:44,255 --> 00:13:45,588
You should alternate between the two.

367
00:13:45,588 --> 00:13:46,822
You need to eat rice too.

368
00:13:46,922 --> 00:13:48,588
Pretend to scoop up the egg
and give him the rice.

369
00:13:48,588 --> 00:13:49,588
Okay.

370
00:13:49,888 --> 00:13:50,888
Pretend getting it.

371
00:13:54,122 --> 00:13:55,922
(Egg!)

372
00:13:57,655 --> 00:13:59,022
(This actually works.)

373
00:13:59,022 --> 00:14:00,288
Just eat it. It's still tasty.

374
00:14:02,822 --> 00:14:03,622
(More.)

375
00:14:03,622 --> 00:14:05,522
All right. He got tricked once,
so he wants the egg.

376
00:14:05,522 --> 00:14:07,022
- We'll give it now.
- He'll alternate between the two.

377
00:14:07,022 --> 00:14:08,288
(I'd better eat quickly.)

378
00:14:08,288 --> 00:14:09,522
Yu Jun, finish the bite first.

379
00:14:09,988 --> 00:14:10,988
Finish it first.

380
00:14:11,822 --> 00:14:12,855
Swallow it.

381
00:14:13,155 --> 00:14:14,288
Okay, you're ready.

382
00:14:14,288 --> 00:14:15,422
(Our Yu Jun is such a good boy!)

383
00:14:15,422 --> 00:14:16,622
This is so funny.

384
00:14:18,055 --> 00:14:19,188
(Picking the rice for once)

385
00:14:19,188 --> 00:14:20,222
It's rice this time?

386
00:14:20,522 --> 00:14:23,222
Yes. The rice tastes good
with lots of dried seaweed.

387
00:14:23,655 --> 00:14:24,722
(Giving it quickly)

388
00:14:24,722 --> 00:14:25,722
(I'll just have the egg.)

389
00:14:25,722 --> 00:14:27,155
- No?
- Pretend to get it.

390
00:14:27,155 --> 00:14:29,288
(Then we can pretend
to scoop it up again.)

391
00:14:29,488 --> 00:14:31,122
(Here, I scooped it up!)

392
00:14:32,855 --> 00:14:35,255
(He fell for it twice.)

393
00:14:35,355 --> 00:14:36,755
(Delicious!)

394
00:14:36,755 --> 00:14:37,822
Tasty, right?

395
00:14:38,255 --> 00:14:40,022
- How naive.
- You have no idea what you ate.

396
00:14:41,322 --> 00:14:42,588
(Uncles have a quick meal.)

397
00:14:42,588 --> 00:14:44,055
(Huh?)

398
00:14:44,088 --> 00:14:45,722
(What are you eating, Uncle?)

399
00:14:46,422 --> 00:14:47,422
(Eye contact)

400
00:14:48,222 --> 00:14:49,222
(What was that cute face just now?)
Feeling great?

401
00:14:51,655 --> 00:14:52,722
Are you happy?

402
00:14:53,188 --> 00:14:54,855
(Eye contact with the camera too)

403
00:14:55,655 --> 00:14:56,755
(One more bite using the egg trick)

404
00:14:56,755 --> 00:14:57,755
Here.

405
00:14:57,755 --> 00:14:58,788
Hold on.

406
00:14:58,888 --> 00:15:00,555
(What a cute boy.)

407
00:15:01,388 --> 00:15:04,088
(Let me have a bite too.)

408
00:15:04,722 --> 00:15:06,255
(Give me more.)

409
00:15:06,988 --> 00:15:08,855
(The spoon is returned to SOOBIN.)

410
00:15:09,355 --> 00:15:10,688
(Shaking his head)

411
00:15:10,688 --> 00:15:11,922
What?

412
00:15:12,388 --> 00:15:13,388
He gets possessed sometimes.

413
00:15:13,488 --> 00:15:15,588
Sometimes he looks up at the sky
and shakes his head.

414
00:15:15,588 --> 00:15:16,588
I know.

415
00:15:16,588 --> 00:15:17,722
Does it taste that good?

416
00:15:18,588 --> 00:15:20,222
(Can't resist and takes a big bite)

417
00:15:21,222 --> 00:15:22,788
It just tastes like a konjac jelly.

418
00:15:23,188 --> 00:15:24,355
He doesn't want you stealing it.

419
00:15:24,355 --> 00:15:25,788
- No flavor?
- Fine.

420
00:15:29,455 --> 00:15:30,555
(Tasting)

421
00:15:30,555 --> 00:15:32,222
All right.

422
00:15:32,822 --> 00:15:34,288
Okay.

423
00:15:35,322 --> 00:15:36,788
(Have you ever seen a baby
with such a huge appetite?)

424
00:15:36,788 --> 00:15:37,822
- Such a good eater.
- Nice.

425
00:15:38,722 --> 00:15:40,422
Don't you think he'd be full by now?

426
00:15:40,788 --> 00:15:42,388
- He ate a lot.
- I bet Yu Jun...

427
00:15:42,388 --> 00:15:43,755
has no idea when he's full.

428
00:15:44,122 --> 00:15:45,222
He should eat a lot while he's young.

429
00:15:45,555 --> 00:15:46,855
So he can grow tall like us.

430
00:15:46,855 --> 00:15:47,855
Right.

431
00:15:48,322 --> 00:15:49,655
He's leaning forward.

432
00:15:49,655 --> 00:15:51,555
(Food, here I come.)

433
00:15:52,688 --> 00:15:53,855
(This too.)

434
00:15:54,988 --> 00:15:56,255
I'm sure he'll grow up tall.

435
00:15:56,255 --> 00:15:58,488
I saw his dad, and he's pretty tall.

436
00:15:58,488 --> 00:16:00,655
He likes running around,
so he'll grow up just fine.

437
00:16:00,922 --> 00:16:02,022
Does it make you clap?

438
00:16:03,422 --> 00:16:05,555
(A bite of egg, his favorite food)

439
00:16:05,888 --> 00:16:07,455
(Water!)

440
00:16:07,455 --> 00:16:08,455
Does he want water?

441
00:16:10,322 --> 00:16:12,022
(Water?)

442
00:16:12,022 --> 00:16:13,088
(You want water?)

443
00:16:14,422 --> 00:16:15,422
You want me to pour some?
What do I do?

444
00:16:16,588 --> 00:16:17,588
Okay, then.

445
00:16:17,855 --> 00:16:18,988
(That one too!)

446
00:16:18,988 --> 00:16:20,022
I think that's the one.

447
00:16:20,255 --> 00:16:21,255
This?

448
00:16:21,688 --> 00:16:22,855
(Yes.)

449
00:16:23,355 --> 00:16:25,222
(Give me my cup!)

450
00:16:25,888 --> 00:16:26,988
Okay.

451
00:16:27,688 --> 00:16:28,855
All right.

452
00:16:28,855 --> 00:16:31,222
- He wanted to drink water.
- Then we're taking a break for now.

453
00:16:31,222 --> 00:16:32,388
Eat.

454
00:16:32,388 --> 00:16:34,722
Right. Yu Jun takes a long time
to drink water.

455
00:16:35,355 --> 00:16:39,788
(Uncles quickly finish their meals
while he drinks water.)

456
00:16:40,622 --> 00:16:41,988
(Sucking)

457
00:16:42,455 --> 00:16:43,455
(Refreshed)

458
00:16:43,888 --> 00:16:46,022
(Uncles, Yu Jun finished his water.)

459
00:16:46,022 --> 00:16:47,122
Let's eat, Yu Jun.

460
00:16:47,122 --> 00:16:48,188
(Let's eat with Uncle HUENINGKAI now.)

461
00:16:48,355 --> 00:16:49,388
Food.

462
00:16:49,588 --> 00:16:51,722
Yu Jun couldn't get a proper nap
even though he was sleepy.

463
00:16:51,822 --> 00:16:52,855
He'll be out when we get back.

464
00:16:52,855 --> 00:16:54,055
- Exactly.
- There.

465
00:16:54,622 --> 00:16:55,888
(There's no egg.)

466
00:16:56,122 --> 00:16:58,155
(Then we'll use the deception trick.)

467
00:16:58,688 --> 00:17:00,088
- It's not working now.
- He's not falling for it anymore.

468
00:17:00,322 --> 00:17:01,755
I put the egg on it.

469
00:17:03,088 --> 00:17:04,155
(Opening up)

470
00:17:04,488 --> 00:17:06,622
- You just need to put the egg.
- Yes, it works with the egg on it.

471
00:17:06,622 --> 00:17:07,622
(Don't forget to add the egg.)

472
00:17:07,688 --> 00:17:10,522
- He likes it with the egg.
- Right, he likes it that way.

473
00:17:10,988 --> 00:17:12,355
He's well-behaved in the car too.

474
00:17:13,555 --> 00:17:15,155
Good. Sorry.

475
00:17:15,455 --> 00:17:16,622
He dropped it.

476
00:17:16,622 --> 00:17:17,755
(I feel awesome.)

477
00:17:17,755 --> 00:17:19,055
Delicious, right?

478
00:17:20,222 --> 00:17:21,255
Do you like it?

479
00:17:22,888 --> 00:17:25,288
(He turns into a dolphin
when he's in a good mood.)

480
00:17:25,622 --> 00:17:26,988
(Hehe, this is fun!)

481
00:17:27,322 --> 00:17:28,388
He's feeling great.

482
00:17:28,488 --> 00:17:29,622
He's having the best time today.

483
00:17:30,288 --> 00:17:32,688
(Of course I am.)

484
00:17:32,688 --> 00:17:33,922
Private Choi Yu Jun!

485
00:17:34,722 --> 00:17:35,755
Say, "Ack!"

486
00:17:35,922 --> 00:17:37,688
You'll only answer with "Ack."

487
00:17:39,622 --> 00:17:41,155
(Babbling)

488
00:17:41,755 --> 00:17:43,422
(Hehe, this is funny.)

489
00:17:44,155 --> 00:17:45,722
(That startled me.)

490
00:17:45,722 --> 00:17:47,088
(Babbling)

491
00:17:47,455 --> 00:17:48,788
(Let's see.)

492
00:17:49,155 --> 00:17:50,222
Yu Jun, what's this?

493
00:17:50,255 --> 00:17:52,155
- Arm.
- Yes, an arm.

494
00:17:52,522 --> 00:17:54,388
- Can he even speak English?
- He's talented.

495
00:17:54,388 --> 00:17:56,322
- He's already speaking another language?
- No way!

496
00:17:56,488 --> 00:17:57,522
He speaks English better than I do.

497
00:17:58,788 --> 00:18:00,288
- Arm.
- Arm.

498
00:18:00,955 --> 00:18:02,222
Drink it and go, "Ahh."

499
00:18:03,088 --> 00:18:04,188
Say, "Ahh."

500
00:18:05,255 --> 00:18:06,255
(Our baby is really a genius.)

501
00:18:06,255 --> 00:18:08,855
- He's good.
- I feel like we can talk to you now.

502
00:18:08,855 --> 00:18:10,122
- Yes.
- Now we can.

503
00:18:10,688 --> 00:18:11,788
Are you done, Yu Jun?

504
00:18:11,788 --> 00:18:13,755
Say, "Thank you for the meal."

505
00:18:13,755 --> 00:18:15,188
- Thank you for the meal.
- Thank you for the meal.

506
00:18:15,655 --> 00:18:16,655
Thank you for the meal.

507
00:18:18,022 --> 00:18:22,755
(May 8, Parents' Day, a special guest)

508
00:18:23,822 --> 00:18:27,255
(The three already look busy
this morning.)

509
00:18:27,755 --> 00:18:31,488
(Preparing for a Parents' Day event
featuring a special guest)

510
00:18:32,588 --> 00:18:36,222
(In charge of the balloons
and in charge of the drawings)

511
00:18:37,422 --> 00:18:41,955
(Where are YEONJUN, TAEHYUN, and Yu Jun?)

512
00:18:47,655 --> 00:18:48,988
What a lovely weather, Yu Jun.

513
00:18:48,988 --> 00:18:50,655
(Having a walk with Yu Jun
since the weather is nice)

514
00:18:50,655 --> 00:18:51,788
Hello, Yu Jun.

515
00:18:52,122 --> 00:18:53,988
Bang!

516
00:18:55,055 --> 00:18:57,555
He's walking so much better now!

517
00:18:58,155 --> 00:18:59,155
Pass!

518
00:19:00,255 --> 00:19:01,255
(A ball game!)

519
00:19:01,255 --> 00:19:02,322
That's it.

520
00:19:02,422 --> 00:19:03,855
(Father and son can have fun
with just a ball.)

521
00:19:03,855 --> 00:19:04,955
Pass.

522
00:19:06,722 --> 00:19:07,722
(I'm passing too!)
Good!

523
00:19:09,522 --> 00:19:10,555
You're kicking it.

524
00:19:10,555 --> 00:19:11,755
(Wobbling)

525
00:19:12,422 --> 00:19:15,188
(Way to go, Yu Jun.)

526
00:19:16,488 --> 00:19:17,488
Yu Jun.

527
00:19:17,888 --> 00:19:19,288
(TAEHYUN brought a bubble wand.)

528
00:19:19,555 --> 00:19:20,955
(Bubbles!)

529
00:19:21,188 --> 00:19:22,188
He likes it.

530
00:19:22,188 --> 00:19:23,455
(A quick U-turn after seeing bubbles)

531
00:19:23,522 --> 00:19:24,522
He loves it.

532
00:19:26,688 --> 00:19:27,855
You can't say no to this, right?

533
00:19:28,722 --> 00:19:30,722
So you like bubbles, Yu Jun.

534
00:19:33,755 --> 00:19:35,022
(Me too.)

535
00:19:35,022 --> 00:19:36,055
You want to play?

536
00:19:38,288 --> 00:19:41,088
(Back to Yu Jun's favorite toy cart)

537
00:19:42,388 --> 00:19:43,822
(A tiny hand shows up.)

538
00:19:45,755 --> 00:19:48,255
(He defeated Uncle YEONJUN!)

539
00:19:48,888 --> 00:19:49,888
Bonk.

540
00:19:50,555 --> 00:19:51,555
Bonk!

541
00:19:53,622 --> 00:19:54,955
Yu Jun, bonk again.

542
00:19:55,088 --> 00:19:56,088
- Bonk!
- Bonk!

543
00:19:56,088 --> 00:19:57,955
(It's a comedy in long-shot...)

544
00:19:57,955 --> 00:20:00,288
(and also a comedy when seen in close-up.)

545
00:20:00,766 --> 00:20:02,833
(YEONJUN is keeping Yu Jun entertained
with his whole body.)

546
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:04,266
He's having the best time right now.

547
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:09,966
(YEONJUN is knocked out.)

548
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:12,866
(Yu Jun, a 16-month-old baby,
is so strong.)

549
00:20:12,866 --> 00:20:14,000
How did you lift that?

550
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:15,566
Yu Jun is super strong.

551
00:20:22,866 --> 00:20:23,900
Do you want to drink some water?

552
00:20:26,800 --> 00:20:28,100
All right. Good?

553
00:20:28,333 --> 00:20:29,400
Have a sip.

554
00:20:34,766 --> 00:20:37,033
Look, Yu Jun.

555
00:20:37,800 --> 00:20:38,866
You find this funny?

556
00:20:38,866 --> 00:20:39,766
Right.

557
00:20:39,766 --> 00:20:42,433
(Suddenly breaking into a krump dance)

558
00:20:42,433 --> 00:20:43,300
Stomp your foot on the ground.

559
00:20:44,266 --> 00:20:46,566
(Yu Jun, follow TAEHYUN's moves.)

560
00:20:47,233 --> 00:20:49,366
(Stomping)

561
00:20:49,366 --> 00:20:50,233
So cute.

562
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:54,966
(It's time for head-shaking now.)

563
00:20:57,866 --> 00:20:59,666
(Shaking his head, following YEONJUN.)

564
00:20:59,666 --> 00:21:00,600
He seems possessed.

565
00:21:02,966 --> 00:21:03,866
Yu Jun.

566
00:21:04,333 --> 00:21:07,866
(Yu Jun's head shake is
too cute not to film.)

567
00:21:09,100 --> 00:21:10,066
One more time, please.

568
00:21:10,933 --> 00:21:11,800
Yu Jun.

569
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:14,600
(Doting uncles
completely smitten with Yu Jun)

570
00:21:14,866 --> 00:21:16,800
Yu Jun, shake your head.

571
00:21:17,966 --> 00:21:18,766
Shake your head.

572
00:21:18,766 --> 00:21:20,933
(Waiting for the fancam)

573
00:21:21,433 --> 00:21:24,033
(Encore head shake)

574
00:21:24,233 --> 00:21:26,300
(Giggling)

575
00:21:26,700 --> 00:21:27,633
Yu Jun, high five!

576
00:21:28,500 --> 00:21:29,300
High five.

577
00:21:29,300 --> 00:21:31,100
(High five!)

578
00:21:32,300 --> 00:21:33,266
He's so excited.

579
00:21:38,233 --> 00:21:42,333
(On Parents' Day, Yu Jun is showing
his love through cuteness.)

580
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:44,033
I should put this on the wall.

581
00:21:44,033 --> 00:21:45,333
(Meanwhile, the Parents' Day
home party prep team)

582
00:21:45,333 --> 00:21:46,566
I already put it on the back.

583
00:21:46,566 --> 00:21:47,433
Good.

584
00:21:48,233 --> 00:21:52,133
(They wrote the letters themselves.)

585
00:21:53,166 --> 00:21:56,533
(Putting them up
where everyone can see them)

586
00:21:56,533 --> 00:21:58,233
(Everyone is busy with their task.)

587
00:21:58,233 --> 00:22:00,633
By the way,
we're not the only ones eating.

588
00:22:00,633 --> 00:22:03,233
We should order plenty
so there's enough for everyone.

589
00:22:04,333 --> 00:22:06,400
I wonder what kind of food they like.

590
00:22:07,558 --> 00:22:10,400
He's known for being a big foodie,

591
00:22:10,400 --> 00:22:14,100
so there isn't really one specific food
that's known as his favorite.

592
00:22:15,733 --> 00:22:17,233
I guess he enjoys pretty much anything.

593
00:22:17,233 --> 00:22:19,233
He talks about food a lot,

594
00:22:19,233 --> 00:22:20,700
and tteokbokki and gimbap are...

595
00:22:20,700 --> 00:22:22,200
known to be his favorites.

596
00:22:22,200 --> 00:22:24,433
- Nice job.
- Good.

597
00:22:24,433 --> 00:22:25,500
(We also had a nice walk.)

598
00:22:25,500 --> 00:22:26,666
That was a really nice walk.

599
00:22:28,700 --> 00:22:30,500
- Let's go wash our hands.
- Yu Jun, let's take your shirt off.

600
00:22:31,466 --> 00:22:32,833
He's taking it off all by himself?

601
00:22:32,833 --> 00:22:33,866
I know. He does on his own.

602
00:22:33,866 --> 00:22:34,966
He can do it by himself.

603
00:22:35,333 --> 00:22:37,133
He must be really hot
after running around so much.

604
00:22:37,133 --> 00:22:38,233
His body is hot.

605
00:22:38,733 --> 00:22:39,800
He ran up and down all those hills.

606
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:40,966
Let me wipe your hands.
Yu Jun.

607
00:22:42,333 --> 00:22:43,700
(It's cold.)

608
00:22:44,500 --> 00:22:47,366
(Guys always entertain a kid
in a goofy way.)

609
00:22:48,133 --> 00:22:52,233
(Meanwhile, the cleaning master is
wiping down the cart wheels.)

610
00:22:52,233 --> 00:22:53,900
(Mr. Clean)

611
00:22:55,533 --> 00:22:57,366
No, wait. Let me clean this first.

612
00:22:57,366 --> 00:22:58,333
It's dirty.

613
00:22:58,766 --> 00:23:01,066
Wait a minute.

614
00:23:01,500 --> 00:23:03,366
(Can I play now?)

615
00:23:04,600 --> 00:23:06,900
He's in such a good mood.
He was running around outside yelling.

616
00:23:06,900 --> 00:23:08,166
- Really?
- He did?

617
00:23:08,166 --> 00:23:10,266
- He was really yelling like this...
- Right.

618
00:23:10,266 --> 00:23:11,300
- and waving his hands.
- He must've been so excited.

619
00:23:11,933 --> 00:23:13,366
My nephew does the exact same thing.

620
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:15,833
(Making a baby sound)

621
00:23:15,833 --> 00:23:17,600
(Let me show you how I played outside.)

622
00:23:17,600 --> 00:23:19,233
- Are you excited?
- Look at him running around.

623
00:23:19,700 --> 00:23:20,800
He runs well.

624
00:23:22,366 --> 00:23:24,666
- Yu Jun, stomp your feet!
- Stomp!

625
00:23:25,700 --> 00:23:26,633
He even repeats what you say.

626
00:23:27,466 --> 00:23:29,666
(Balloon playtime)

627
00:23:30,433 --> 00:23:32,100
(Powerful shot!)

628
00:23:33,233 --> 00:23:34,633
He's throwing it with all his might.

629
00:23:36,300 --> 00:23:37,366
Will it work on Yu Jun too?

630
00:23:38,033 --> 00:23:41,166
(Playing with static electricity
using Yu Jun's hair)

631
00:23:41,766 --> 00:23:43,633
- Stomp!
- Stomp!

632
00:23:44,266 --> 00:23:45,833
(Oops, I missed the balloon.)

633
00:23:48,400 --> 00:23:51,066
(Showing his appreciation
through eye contact)

634
00:23:52,166 --> 00:23:53,066
Why are you so cute?

635
00:23:53,067 --> 00:23:54,114
(Charging up static)

636
00:23:54,200 --> 00:23:55,366
Stomp!

637
00:23:56,795 --> 00:23:58,599
(Look at my hair floating!)

638
00:23:58,600 --> 00:23:59,800
Look at his hair.

639
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:04,133
(My cuteness antenna has been exposed.)

640
00:24:04,633 --> 00:24:06,133
Stomp! Good job.

641
00:24:06,133 --> 00:24:07,133
Good boy.

642
00:24:08,100 --> 00:24:09,766
(Peak dopamine with just one balloon!)

643
00:24:09,766 --> 00:24:10,800
Do you like it that much?

644
00:24:11,333 --> 00:24:13,633
I've never seen Yu Jun
this excited before.

645
00:24:13,633 --> 00:24:14,933
He's so excited right now.

646
00:24:15,366 --> 00:24:16,300
Stomp.

647
00:24:20,533 --> 00:24:21,366
(Get it!)
That's it.

648
00:24:22,300 --> 00:24:23,800
(Giggling)

649
00:24:26,700 --> 00:24:28,633
Let's send all our balloons up for Yu Jun.

650
00:24:32,600 --> 00:24:36,000
(Sending balloons toward Yu Jun)

651
00:24:36,633 --> 00:24:37,600
Stomp!

652
00:24:39,833 --> 00:24:41,800
Yu Jun, you must be super happy.

653
00:24:41,800 --> 00:24:43,466
- It's a balloon party.
- There are balloons everywhere.

654
00:24:44,633 --> 00:24:46,400
There are so many balloons, right?

655
00:24:46,400 --> 00:24:48,533
(He has finally found something
as fun as the cart.)

656
00:24:48,866 --> 00:24:50,833
(TAEHYUN joins.)

657
00:24:51,633 --> 00:24:53,700
(Lifting the balloons over Yu Jun again)

658
00:24:53,700 --> 00:24:54,666
It's chaotic, isn't it?

659
00:24:55,066 --> 00:24:56,133
His eyes are so big...

660
00:24:56,133 --> 00:24:57,733
that you can see
every little eye movement.

661
00:24:57,733 --> 00:24:59,333
Are you happy?

662
00:25:00,433 --> 00:25:02,000
I guess he likes the sound of the word.

663
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:03,866
- Stomp.
- He must find it fun.

664
00:25:03,866 --> 00:25:05,433
- Stomp.
- Stomp.

665
00:25:10,233 --> 00:25:11,466
It looks so fun.

666
00:25:11,466 --> 00:25:14,933
(Yu Jun is in the best mood today.)

667
00:25:16,300 --> 00:25:17,166
Yu Jun.

668
00:25:18,400 --> 00:25:19,233
Don't cry.

669
00:25:19,233 --> 00:25:21,100
- His mood is at its peak right now.
- You chose it.

670
00:25:21,900 --> 00:25:26,366
(Childish, but they sure know
how to keep a kid happy.)

671
00:25:27,133 --> 00:25:28,033
(Bell ringing)

672
00:25:28,033 --> 00:25:30,200
(Wait.)

673
00:25:30,500 --> 00:25:31,800
(The special Parents' Day guests
have arrived.)

674
00:25:31,800 --> 00:25:32,666
Yu Jun, let's go say hi.

675
00:25:33,666 --> 00:25:35,566
(TAEHYUN hurries to greet them.)

676
00:25:35,900 --> 00:25:39,633
- Hello.
- Hi.

677
00:25:39,633 --> 00:25:40,600
Someone is here.

678
00:25:40,600 --> 00:25:42,800
- Hi.
- Welcome!

679
00:25:43,366 --> 00:25:46,466
- Hello.
- Yu Jun, say hi to them.

680
00:25:46,466 --> 00:25:48,233
- He just bowed.
- Say hi.

681
00:25:48,233 --> 00:25:51,033
(Who are today's special guests?)

682
00:25:51,266 --> 00:25:52,600
You didn't teach him manners, did you?

683
00:25:52,600 --> 00:25:54,066
(The original babysitting idols, god)

684
00:25:54,066 --> 00:25:55,466
All he does is give a little bow.

685
00:25:56,033 --> 00:25:57,066
He just nods his head.

686
00:25:57,066 --> 00:25:59,700
That's the kind of voice
babies don't like.

687
00:26:01,500 --> 00:26:04,366
(Mischievous Uncle Kim Tae Woo
and the forever Mom, Son Ho Young)

688
00:26:04,800 --> 00:26:07,466
(The hit variety show of the early 2000s,
"god's Baby Diary")

689
00:26:09,533 --> 00:26:12,733
(The stars of the original parenting show
have come!)

690
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:15,866
- Are you Yu Jun?
- He is.

691
00:26:15,866 --> 00:26:17,566
Hello.

692
00:26:17,566 --> 00:26:19,100
- I brought you a little gift.
- We brought you a gift.

693
00:26:19,100 --> 00:26:21,266
- They got you a gift.
- Good for you.

694
00:26:21,800 --> 00:26:24,966
You've never seen
someone with a beard, right?

695
00:26:24,966 --> 00:26:26,766
You're making him back away.

696
00:26:28,466 --> 00:26:29,700
- You don't want the gift?
- Let's look at the gift.

697
00:26:29,700 --> 00:26:32,466
Let's hand it over to the members.

698
00:26:32,466 --> 00:26:33,466
What's this?

699
00:26:33,766 --> 00:26:34,766
I saw in the videos...

700
00:26:34,766 --> 00:26:37,733
- that he likes pushing a cart around.
- It's his favorite.

701
00:26:37,733 --> 00:26:39,000
Yu Jun, you got a brand new cart.

702
00:26:39,666 --> 00:26:41,233
- Amazing.
- You've got a new cart!

703
00:26:43,700 --> 00:26:45,566
(They're completely captivated
by Yu Jun's new cart.)

704
00:26:45,566 --> 00:26:46,600
It's so cute.

705
00:26:49,266 --> 00:26:50,466
He's way cuter in person.

706
00:26:50,466 --> 00:26:53,400
(These two are completely captivated
by Yu Jun.)

707
00:26:54,133 --> 00:26:55,666
Yu Jun, ready to try out your new cart?

708
00:26:57,566 --> 00:26:59,533
You've never seen someone like him before,
have you?

709
00:26:59,533 --> 00:27:01,800
(You've never seen
someone this big before, right?)

710
00:27:01,966 --> 00:27:03,266
- Let's wash our hands first.
- Right.

711
00:27:03,266 --> 00:27:04,833
You have new babysitters.

712
00:27:04,833 --> 00:27:06,200
You're curious about that guy, aren't you?

713
00:27:08,500 --> 00:27:09,400
Hello.

714
00:27:10,033 --> 00:27:11,800
- You're shy, aren't you?
- Hi, Yu Jun.

715
00:27:11,800 --> 00:27:13,400
- Say hi.
- Hello.

716
00:27:14,100 --> 00:27:15,166
Hi.

717
00:27:15,766 --> 00:27:16,733
Do you want this?

718
00:27:19,100 --> 00:27:21,300
- Stomp.
- Stomp.

719
00:27:21,300 --> 00:27:24,433
- That's it!
- We do the same thing all the time.

720
00:27:24,433 --> 00:27:26,433
- He's interested in him.
- You're a real veteran.

721
00:27:27,733 --> 00:27:28,966
(Calming his nerves with some cheese)

722
00:27:28,966 --> 00:27:30,400
You like cheese?

723
00:27:31,433 --> 00:27:33,066
Is it good?

724
00:27:33,733 --> 00:27:35,566
Why did you choose
such a challenging journey?

725
00:27:37,500 --> 00:27:40,200
- Yu Jun, want to come over to me?
- That's a new face, Yu Jun.

726
00:27:40,200 --> 00:27:42,233
- Let's go to him.
- I have three kids.

727
00:27:43,300 --> 00:27:45,366
(Don't come any closer!)

728
00:27:46,400 --> 00:27:48,700
Even after all these years,
this never changes.

729
00:27:48,700 --> 00:27:50,033
Yu Jun, look at him.

730
00:27:50,033 --> 00:27:51,266
He's a new uncle.

731
00:27:51,266 --> 00:27:52,100
Look at his face.

732
00:27:52,433 --> 00:27:53,866
My kids liked me when they were little.

733
00:27:54,433 --> 00:27:55,600
(That's because you're their dad.)

734
00:27:55,600 --> 00:27:56,766
Want to come over to me?

735
00:27:56,766 --> 00:27:59,200
- Come.
- He really got down low for you.

736
00:27:59,200 --> 00:28:01,100
- It's better, isn't it?
- Want to touch my beard?

737
00:28:01,566 --> 00:28:02,700
(Your beard?)

738
00:28:02,700 --> 00:28:04,033
Isn't it so fascinating? Look.

739
00:28:04,033 --> 00:28:05,533
(A brand new way of beard flirting)

740
00:28:05,533 --> 00:28:06,400
He finds it interesting.
Try pulling on his beard.

741
00:28:07,400 --> 00:28:08,366
Isn't it fascinating?

742
00:28:09,533 --> 00:28:10,600
It's funny, isn't it?

743
00:28:10,600 --> 00:28:13,466
(The Parents' Day home party hits
a snag right from the start.)
